{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Praise the Lord! For it is good to sing praises to our God; for it is pleasant, and a song of praise is fitting."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "A Psalm of Praise"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The Lord builds up Jerusalem; he gathers the outcasts of Israel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "wounds: Heb. griefs"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He determines the number of the stars; he gives to all of them their names."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Great is our Lord, and abundant in power; his understanding is beyond measure."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "his understanding there is no number"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The Lord lifts up the humble; he casts the wicked down to the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Sing to the Lord with thanksgiving; make melody to our God on the lyre."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He covers the heavens with clouds; he prepares rain for the earth; he makes grass grow on the hills."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He gives to the beasts their food, and to the young ravens that cry."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His delight is not in the strength of the horse, nor his pleasure in the legs of a man."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The Lord takes pleasure in those who fear him, in those who hope in his steadfast love."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Praise the Lord, O Jerusalem! Praise your God, O Zion!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For he strengthens the bars of your gates; he blesses your children within you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He makes peace in your borders; he fills you with the finest of the wheat."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Who maketh thy border peace",
        "finest of wheat"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He sends out his command to the earth; his word runs swiftly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He gives snow like wool; he scatters frost like ashes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He hurls down his crystal of ice like crumbs; who can stand before his cold?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He sends out his word, and melts them; he makes his wind blow and the waters flow."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He declares his word to Jacob, his statutes and rules to Israel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "his word: Heb. his words"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has not dealt thus with any other nation; they do not know his rules. Praise the Lord!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}